0 GAIN~
The gain command is used to learn new skills, once the proper trainer has 
been found. (The sailor at Midgaard, From Recall : 2 South, 3 East, South) 
The following options can be used with gain:

UNUSED gain list:    list all groups and skills that can be learned
gain skills:  list all skills that can be learned
gain spells:  list all spells that can be learned
gain powers:  list all powers that can be learned
gain songs :  list all songs that can be learned
gain groups:  list all groups that can be learned
gain points:  lower your creation points by 1 (costs two sessions)
gain <name>:  add a skill or skill group, at the listed cost
gain convert: turns 10 practices into one training session
gain revert:  turns 1 train into 10 practices

Gain uses training sessions, not practices. (see 'help train')
Gained skills and groups do NOT increase your experience per level or total
number of creation points. 
~

0 SKILLS SPELLS POWERS SONGS~
The skills, spells and powers commands are used to display your character's 
list of available skills (or spells or power, as the case may be).  They are 
listed in order of level, with mana/psp cost (for spells/powers) or percentage 
(for skills) listed where applicable.
Syntax:
 spells        will display spells you have from lvl 1 to your current lvl
 skills all    will display skills you have from lvl 1 to max level
 powers 50     will display powers you have from lvl 1 to lvl 50
 skills 3 60   will display skills you have from lvl 3 to lvl 60
 songs 50      will display songs you have from lvl 1 to lvl 50

See also help about individuals skills, spells, powers and songs.
And also about use, cast, psi and sing.
~


0 OUTFIT~
The outfit command, usable by levels 5 and below, equips your character with
a new set of sub issue gear (banner, weapon, helmet, shield, and vest), 
courtesy of the Mayor's warehouses.  Only empty equipment slots are affected.
~

0 AUTO AUTOLIST AUTOLOOT AUTOGOLD AUTOSAC AUTOEXIT AUTOASSIST AUTOSPLIT AUTOTICK AUTOAFFECT~
ROM uses varies automatic actions, to ease the boredom of always splitting
gold and sacrificing corpses.  The commands are as follows:

autolist  : list all automatic actions
autoloot  : take all equipment from dead mobiles
autogold  : take all gold from dead mobiles
autosac   : sacrifice dead monsters (if autoloot is on, only empty corpes)
autoexit  : display room exits upon entering a room
autosplit : split up spoils from combat among your group members
autoassit : makes you help group members in combat
autoaffect: display your affects when looking your score
autotitle : your title change when you gain a level
autotick  : you receive 'TICK' each tick

Typing a command sets the action , typing it again removes it. 
~ 

-1 CLAN~
   A Clan is a collection of players, united to  follow and further
a common cause. Each clan has rules and  regulations, to find out
more about clans and their 'beliefs' type "help <clan name>".
To join a Clan you must be level 10 or above (clan leaders decide).

Type 'help petition' to see how to join a clan.

If you go Loner before level 25 you may join a Clan later.
   Joining a Clan is a dangerous step. Many adventurers live to 
kill and torture others and chances are that your paths will cross.
Remember, attacking or killing fellow clan members *IS* illegal except to 
mutiny your Clan leader.
   Existing Clans may buy special rooms and mobiles by acquiring 
gold as payment.  To see room prices, type "help upgrade".  
New Clans may be formed by petitioning the immortals. Please remember that 
their word is final on all matters not covered by this help.
~

0 PETITION~
For Players :

Syntax : petition <clan name>

If you want to enter a clan, you could "send" a petition to the leader.
Without petition no leader could "force" you to enter his clan.
Then he'll decide to accept or reject your petition.

For Leaders :

Syntax : petition
It shows you people who have send a petition to your clan

Syntax : petition accept <player>
It allows you to add the player (if he sent you a petition).

Syntax : petition reject <player>
Reject the petition of the player.

Syntax : petition remove <player>
Drops a player from the clan.

Syntax : petition raise <player> <status>
Promote a clan member. 
Available status are : Second, Deputy, Senior, Junior.
~

0 COUNT~
The count command displays the number of people (that you can see) logged
into the mud.  It also displays the highest number observed that day, if
it is higher.
~ 

0 MULTICLASS~
Syntax: multiclass <Class>

When you've reached level 100, you become HERO. But after a time ...
beeing hero starts to be boring. Now you could multiclass. When you 
multiclass, you've to choose a new class (another than your actual one).
You could multiclass many times you want (and available classes).
When you multiclass, your stats are kept (int, wis, dex ...)and your skills
and spells keep their rating but are only available at the required
level. You lose all your equipment but you get all newbie one.
You stay in your clan too at the same status.
Your XP/level is multiplied by number of classes you have.
So beeing multiclass [Mlt] is a really good value.
If you need more info about multiclassing ask an imm.

Related help: remort
~

0 REMORT~
Syntax: remort <Class>
Not Yet Implemented

Related help: multiclass
~

-1 QUEST~
Quest command is used for automated quest, you need to be in the same room
as a questmaster in order to use it.
The following options can be used with quest:

quest points     : how many QP (quest points) you already have
quest info       : info about your current quest
quest time       : how many time till next quest or until end of current quest
quest request    : ask a quest to a questmaster
quest complete   : inform the questmaster your quest is completed
quest list       : list of quest item you can buy with QP
quest buy <item> : buy a quest item with QP
quest giveup     : give up the quest
~

0 AFFECTS AFFECT~
This command is used to show all the spells affecting your character. At
low levels, only the spell name will be displayed, at higher levels the
effects and duration of the spell will also be shown.  Spell effects
are no longer shown on score(this can be changed by using 'autoaffect' command).
~

-1 SIZE SIZES~
There is 6 sizes available:
tiny: small birds and anything smaller
small: large birds (ducks and up) to halflings
medium: elves and dwarves to humans
large: ogres, gnolls, and other large humanoids
huge: giants, small dragons, and wyverns
giant: for VERY large critters, i.e. dragons, titans, and the biggest giants 
~

0 ALIAS UNALIAS~
Syntax: alias
	alias <word>
	alias <word> <substitution>
	unalias <word>

The alias command allows limited shortening of command names.  At this time,
aliases cannot call other aliases, and cannot generate more than one command.
Alias by itself lists your current aliases, Alias <word> lists the alias with 
that name (if such exist), and alias with both a word and and argument 
produces a new alias.  You cannot alias either alias or unalias to a new
command.  Examples of use:

alias gc get all corpse --> typing gc will equal typing 'get all corpse'
alias ff cast 'fireball' --> ff orc will equal typing 'cast 'fireball' orc'
alias kick use kick --> kick orc will equal typing 'use kick orc'

Only the first word on the line will be subsituted at this time.
~

-1 CONDITION~
Objects can be damaged by spells or during combat, you can repair it in a
repair shop or ask a player who has the repair skill.

This is the different condition:
  perfect    100%
  good       81% - 99%
  awesome    61% - 80%
  worse      41% - 60%
  defect     21% - 40%
  bad         1% - 20%
  ruined      0%  can't be repaired
~

0 BATTLE CHALLENGE BETARENA ARENA AWHO AHALL~
Syntax:
 arena                            to enter in a battle
 betarena <plr name> <gold amt>   to bet on a player in a battle
 challenge <plr name>             to challenge a player
 accept                           to accept a challenge
 decline                          to decline a challenge
 awho                             to people in the battle
 ahall                            to see the hall of fames

Battle can be started by Immortals and allow player to kill other one.
In battle you can kill other players like you were PK, but with any
cost when you die, you don't lose your stuff, xp, ... You don't
get the killer flag, neither experience when killing someone.
(Immortals can check help about 'chaos' to see how to start a battle)

When a battle starts, you receive a msg, then if you want to enter in the
battle you have to type 'arena'
Then you are teleport in a waiting room until the waiting is over.
When the waiting is over, the ground opens and you fall in the battlefield
and you can kill other player.

Players, who don't want to (cannot) enter in battle, can bet on player 
with command 'betarena <player name> <gold amount>'

If a battle is not running, you can also challenge another player in your
level range (+/- 15 levels), you can't challenge a player with less than
hour of play or with a level less than 5, the same condition applies to you.
~

0 KNOCK~
Syntax: knock <direction>

With this command, you can knock on a door, people behind the door,
will hear: someone is knocking on the door. Can be useful for RP.  
~

0 PULL~
Syntax: pull <object>

This command will allow you to pull a lever or any item that can be 
pulled.
~

0 CLANLIST~
Syntax: clanlist

This command lists the current clan available in the mud.
~

0 HOMETOWN~
Syntax: hometown

This command will allow you set your recall point, only a few 
location can be used as recall point, generally it's the temple in
town.
~

0 JOG~
Synax: jog <list of direction>

This command will allow you to run instead of just walking giving
direction.
A list of direction has the form: 2n3wu2snde
And it's equivalent of doing, north 2 times, west 3 times, ...
~

0 ENTER~
Syntax: enter <door/portal name>

This command will allow you to step into (walk through) a door or a 
portal.
~

0 DONATE~
Syntax: donate <object>

Donating objects will send them to a special donation pit.
You may also receive a monetary reward for making a donation.
Players may freely take whatever they find in the donation pit.
~

0 QUIET~
Syntax: quiet

This command allows to toggle between quiet/non quiet mode.
When being in quiet mode, you can only hear say and emote.
~

0 QUOTE~
Syntax: quote <msg>

QUOTE is used to paste exciting events such as massive conquests, as well 
as for quoting anything else worthy of being repeated.
~

0 HINTS~
HINTS is a channel giving advices to newbie.
You can turn it off by simply type HINTS.
~

0 GRATS~
Syntax: grats <msg>

GRATS is used to congratulate players for achievements such as gaining levels.
~

0 QUESTION ANSWER~
Syntax: question <your question>
        answer <your answer>

With these channels, you can ask questions to other players such newbie 
helper. You can turn it off by simply typing QUESTION.
~

0 COMBINE~
Syntax: combine

This command allows to toggle between long and short inventory.
~

0 SCAN~
Syntax: scan

This command allows you to see 3 rooms forward in the 4 directions to
check if there is players/mobs.
~

0 CLANTALK~
Syntax: clantalk <msg>

This channel allows you to talk to other people in the same clan as you.
To turn it off, just type CLANTALK.
~

0 INFO GROUPS~
Syntax: info
        info <group name>
        info all

This command lists you the group you already know and your CP.
You are also allowed to ask the composition of a group, or the list
of every existing groups.
~

0 CHANNELS~
Syntax: channels

Give the list of channel with state for each one: ON/OFF
To turn off a channel, just type the channel itself.
~

0 KILL MURDER~
Syntax: kill <mob name>
        murder <player name>

KILL is used to kill mobiles (monsters) you see all over the world.
To kill other players, you have to use MURDER.
~

0 ALIGNMENT ETHO~
1) Lawful Good     - Lawful Good characters strive for those things that
                     will bring the greatest benefit to the most people
                     and cause the least harm.
2) Neutral Good    - Characters of this alignment believe that a balance of
                     forces is important, but that the concerns of law and
                     chaos do not moderate the need for good.
3) Chaotic Good    - Characters of this alignment are strong individualists
                     marked by a streak of kindness and benevolence.  They
                     believe in all the virtues of goodness and right, but
                     they have little use for laws and regulations.
4) Lawful Neutral  - Order and organization are of paramount importance to
                     characters of this alignmnet.  They believe in a strong,
                     well-ordered government, whether that government is a
                     tyranny or benevolent democracy.
5) Neutral         - True neutral characters believe in the ultimate balance
                     of forces, and they refuse to see actions as either good
                     or evil.  Since the majority of people in the world make
                     judgments, true neutral characters are extremely rare.
6) Chaotic Neutral - Characters of this alignment believe there is not order
                     to anything, including their own actions.  With this as
                     a guiding principle, they tend to follow whatever whim
                     strikes them at the moment.
7) Lawful Evil     - Characters of this alignment believe in using society
                     and it's laws to benefit themselves.  Structure and
                     organization elevate those who deserve to rule as well as
                     provide a clearly defined hierarchy between master and
                     servant.
8) Neutral Evil    - Neutral evil characters are primarily concerned with
                     themselves and their own advancement.  They have no
                     particular objection to working with others or, for that
                     matter, going it on their own.
9) Chaotic Evil    - Chaotic evil characters are the bane of all that is good
                     and organized.  They are motivated by the desire for
                     personal gain and pleasure.  They see absoulutely nothing
                     wrong with taking whatever they want by whatever means
                     possible.
~

