0 CONFIG~
Syntax:  config <specifier> [<modifier>]
 specifiers :
  no arg           : display current configuration
  autolist         : display current configuration
  autoassist       : makes you help group members in combat
  autoexit         : display room exits upon entering a room
  autogold         : take all gold from dead mobiles
  autoloot         : take all equipment from dead mobiles
  autosac          : sacrifice dead monsters (only empty corpse if loot set)
  autosplit        : split up spoils from combat among your group members
  autotitle        : your title change when you gain a level
  autoaffect       : display your affects when looking your score
  autotick         : you receive 'TICK' each tick
  autohaggle       : you automatically use haggle skill when trading
  compact          : removes the extra blank line before your prompt
  prompt           : turn your prompt on or off
  combine          : toggle between long and short inventory
  brief            : show room description when you move around
  color            : toggles color mode on/off
  noloot           : turn your corpse safety from thieves on or off
  nosummon         : turn your immune to summon on or off
  nofollow         : toggle between accepting or not followers.
  scroll [<#lines>]: changes the number of lines the mud sends you in a page
  wimpy [<number>] : sets your wimpy value
This command is a replacement for all the autoXXX commands
~

-1 CUSTOMIZE~
{Y
During customization you have the possibility to get skills/spells/powers 
 one by one, without having to take a whole group. Most spells/powers/skills
 are not included in default group you get when you don't customize, so it's 
 adviced to customize your character.
{Y
Abilities = skills/spells/powers/songs
{YTo show the skills/groups list            : {ytype list
{YTo show the spells list                   : {ytype spell
{YTo show the powers list                   : {ytype power
{YTo show the songs list                    : {ytype song
{YTo show the contain of a group            : {ytype info <group name>
{YTo see help about an ability              : {ytype help <ability name>
{YTo gain an ability                        : {ytype add <ability name>
{YTo remove an ability                      : {ytype drop <ability name>
{YTo see the ability you have already added : {ytype learned
{YTo see the ability you already known      : {ytype known
{YTo finish customization                   : {ytype done
{x
~

-1 ADVERTICE~
{YSilly Names: {yNames such as Gumbo, NIN, Fairymeow, Punk, or Cheezze
{YNames with titles: {yNames such as LordAragon, MasterHyru, SuperTed
{YPhilosophical Names: {yNames such as Honesty, Death, Apathy, Hate, Evil
{YSuperlative Names: {yNames such as BlueFire, CuteLady or DeathBringer
{YNames in all CAPS or mixed CAPS: {yNames such as GARTH, HiRaL, LeToDe
{YNonsense or Unpronouncable Names: {yNames such as Yzzyg, Zifffy , or Kikikik
{YMonster names: {yNames such as Bonedevil, Tanarri, Greatersuccubus

{yAll these kinds of name will not be accepted. Once you have created your
character, you receive the {C[NEWBIE]{y flag until your name has been approved
by the immortal staff.

Need some help creating an acceptable name? In general, pick a name
which you can imagine your character's parents naming him or her. Or Combine
syllables to form a name that sounds good, but create one uncomplicated to
spell. If your name is deemed unacceptable by any Immortal, it will be changed.
{x
~

-1 RESTRICTIONS REQUIREMENTS~
Some items have restrictions which make them unwearable by players with some
races/classes/alignments/etho/attributes(str,int,...)/sex/forms/parts/abilities.
When you try to wear an item with restrictions you don't meet, you'll be unable
to wear it and you'll receive a message like: You don't meet the requirements to
use 'item name'.
~

